Lebedev Sells Bank Stake to Son to Guard Assets, Kommersant Says

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-02-17T05:50:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/lebedev-sells-bank-stake-to-son-to-guard-assets-kommersant-says.html
Russian billionaire  Alexander
Lebedev  sold 15 percent of his National Reserve Bank to his son
Evgeny, Kommersant reported, citing the elder Lebedev.   Alexander Lebedev sold the stake as part of a bid to
safeguard assets from Russian government officials after raids
at his bank in Moscow, the Moscow-based newspaper said, without
citing anyone. Evgeny Lebedev lives in  London , has U.K.
citizenship and runs the Independent and Evening Standard
newspapers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer at 
 hmeyer4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brad Cook at 
